The paper discusses speaker verification using deep neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of speech processing and natural language processing (cs.SD). However, the paper also utilizes deep learning techniques for feature learning and classification, which are common in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the objective function used for training, which is related to information retrieval and similarity metrics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper involves experiments and evaluations, which are common in signal processing and statistical learning (cs.SI).
